commitResults.messageTitle: Update HistoryUtil to better apply Demeter's Law
commitResults.messageBody:
Concrete Memento has a string description that the UndoCommand uses to
provide feedback to user. However, a memento cannot have a string description
when made as it is simply a state of the originator and has no knowledge
of time and change. Hence, the memento's description setter is used by
the modifying Commands to descibe the change occured.

This is problematic as this violates Demeter's Law. The Commands use a
method from the memento from the method from model to set a description.
Furthermore, this complicates the Commands' relationship with Memento as
Commands now directly rely on the Concrete implementations of Memento to
set descriptions.

Let's move the descriptions out of the memento and into HistoryUtil. We
will now store the description of the change, along with the memento, into
HistoryUtil instead. HistoryUtil should directly interface with memento,
while Commands should directly interface with model and HistoryUtil instead.

This will resolve Demeter's Law as a memento's methods are no longer used
by the Commands. Command and Memento classes are also decoupled for better
extension in accordance to the open-close principle.

Misc.
- Changed Momento to Memento (spelling).
- Changed HistoryUtil.store to HistoryUtil.storePast (better name).
- Updated Tests to reflect above changes.
- Updated Commands to reflect above changes.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix behaviour for AddCommandParser and EditCommand parser
commitResults.messageBody:
Allow AddCommandParser to accept inputs with no phone number. This is done by removing `PREFIX_PHONE` as an argument from the `arePrefixesPresent()` method. An additional check then has to be done to check if `PREFIX_PHONE` is found in the input. If it is, we parse the argument with `parsePhone` method from `PaserUtil` class. If not, we set the phone to be the default empty phone from the phone class. The default empty phone is a final static field, and calling the method `getEmptyPhone` will return the same instance of the empty phone.
Additionally, if an empty string or a string containing only white space is passed as an argument to `parsePhone` method, it will also return the default emptyPhone from the phone class.

commitResults.messageTitle: Create withoutEmail method in PersonBuilder class
commitResults.messageBody: Allows us to make a model person without email.

We now allow for emails to be omitted, as such the email prefix can be missing. This causes the expected error message to be different. Previously a missing email prefix meant that the user did not place the prefix before the email, which was compulsory. Now when there is no email prefix we take it that the user does not intend to give the person they are adding an email address.

Added tests for expected person that has no email or empty email field. The parse should be successful.
The missing address prefix test should not be an issue as we allow for no address input.
